### PHP do-while Loop

The `do-while` loop executes the code block once before checking the condition, then repeats as long as the condition is true.

### Syntax

```php
<?php
do {
    // code to execute
} while (condition);
?>
```

### Example

```php
<?php
$i = 1;
do {
    echo "Number: $i<br>";
    $i++;
} while ($i <= 5);
?>
```

### while vs do-while

| Feature | while | do-while |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Condition check | Before execution | After execution |
| Minimum iterations | 0 | 1 |
| Syntax | `while (cond) { }` | `do { } while (cond);` |
| Semicolon | Not needed | Required after while |

```php
<?php
// Guaranteed to run once even if false
$i = 100;
do {
    echo "This runs once";
} while ($i < 10);
?>
```

> **Key Point:** Use `do-while` when you need the code block to execute at least once, regardless of the condition.
